A man believed to be in his 20s was killed when his car overturned on the M1 Higginson Highway near Moorton, Chatsworth, in Durban just after 5am on Sunday morning, paramedics said. Rescue Care paramedics responded to the accident to find that the car had rolled several times before coming to a rest on its roof, spokesman Garrith Jamieson said. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained major injuries. Unfortunately he had passed away before paramedics arrival. He was declared deceased on the scene. At this stage, the cause of the accident was unknown, he said.